cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SD 

This paper is about natural language processing tasks using neural sequence-to-sequence models, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses methods for assessing the quality of the output, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and statistical modeling (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions downstream confidence estimation for machine translation (MT) and automatic speech recognition (ASR), which are both related to computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SD).
